Text.Value: The Tears follow behind it. Rocky bodies tumbling through the Sea of Night. One of them is my crèche: K'liir.
Next time you're able, look to the sky, watch the moon cross it.
Are all githyanki from the Tears?
But enough of this. You are wasting your resting time. Come dawn, we resume our search for a crèche.
Extinguish the Tears? Your dedication to your goddess blinds you to their import.
It's there I first saw a kith'rak mount a red dragon. Where I slit my cousins' throats at the varsh's command.
Yes. Rocky bodies named after a false goddess.
The Tears of Selûne? I've spent many a night observing these celestial bodies.
Perhaps we may see them this eve. Look above, to the Sea of Night.
You are too easily astonished. There is more to this realm than this grassy pebble.
We infiltrated a neogi spelljammer and laid waste to its crew.
The Tears of Selûne? They mar the sky - I'd extinguish them if I could.

RuleGroup.RuleString: CLERIC_SELUNE or PALADIN_SELUNE or REALLY_GALE or REALLY_PLANAR or WIZARD

Text.Value: The Tears of Selûne, you mean?

EditorData.logicalname: Cleric/paladin of Sel/ Gale / Wizard / Planar

Text.Value: 'Only?'
The moonlight shines warmly on us. The breeze caresses our faces.
My entire clutch battled beholders deep within the Eye of the Sky.
Leave.
My entire clutch battled beholders within the Eye of the Sky's tunnels.
G'lyck. I remember who I was in Crèche K'liir.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel looking pensively at the ceiling

Text.Value: The Tears span Toril's sky, vin'iisk. There is more to this realm than this grassy pebble.
Did you only train within the Tears?
Leave.
They rely on strangers' swords, when they should be forging their own.
You mean you come from up there? In the sky?

EditorData.logicalname: Halfling, but not cleric paladin or wizard

Text.Value: The Tears span Toril's sky. There is more to the realm than this grassy pebble, kin.
The Tears span Toril's sky. There is more to the realm than this grassy pebble, vin'iisk.
Your curiosity is to be commended.
Perhaps Faerûn has its value. You shouldn't discount it just yet.
Faerûn isn't so bad. Give it a chance.
Hideous. All of it.
Then perhaps you've unknowingly gazed at my crèche, K'liir, as it tumbled past.
Should you be fortunate, you may see Crèche K'liir tumble past.
Githyanki are hatched in crèches all throughout Realmspace. K'liir is one of many.
What do you mean by 'the Tears'?
We infiltrated a neogi Spelljammer and laid waste to its crew.
Would that I were doing battle up there, among the Tears.
Flowering meadows and fecund soil have softened their minds and muscles.
I was hungry to face my first ghaik, my sword pined for their blood.
A fine evening, don't you think?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~Laezel is looking upward to the sky [lookats]
EditorData.NodeContext: She should sound sincere to begin with, but she twists this around on the third line
EditorData.logicalname: AFTER LEARNING OF OTHER GITH FROM ZORRU

Text.Value: You want to do battle up where?
Look above. Watch the moon cross the sky.
I see naught but cowards cowering in their groves and grottos.
You are wise not to waste your resting time. Come dawn, we resume our search for a crèche.
G'lyck. Sleeping in a cave reminds me of my adolescence - in Crèche K'liir.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel looking resentfully at the ceiling

Text.Value: Do you think me so sheltered?
It must be quite a shock, to leave your crèche behind and arrive here.

Synopsis: Player confronts Lae'zel in camp for the third night of rest. You discuss the solutions in front of you. She is less intense than usual. But she does not like you pointing this out.
